---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 418
  - Title: Brihad-Âranyaka Upanishad
    Location: I iv 10
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Heterodoxy And Deviation=Error
  - 775
---
Whoever worships another divinity (than Âtmâ as identified with
Brahma), thinking, ‘He is one and I another,’ he knows not. He is like
a sacrificial animal for the gods.
